This paper deals with load balancing in cellular networks, which is a topic related to network infrastructure and communication protocols. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also discusses resource allocation and optimization, which are topics related to information theory, making cs.IT (Information Theory) another likely category. The paper proposes a solution that involves D2D communication, which is a topic related to system design and control, making cs.SY (Systems and Control) a possible category. The paper also discusses simulation results, which are related to multimedia and image processing, making cs.MM (Multimedia) a possible category. Finally, the paper discusses security and privacy concerns related to load balancing, which is a topic related to cryptography, making cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) a possible category.
